        <div purpose="subsection" class="mb-0">
          <h2>Summary</h2>
          <p>As we found, the organizations represented by our respondents certainly need ways to manage the multitude of endpoints they have. A quarter of respondents are in organizations managing 250,000 devices or more, and a quarter are in organizations that have over 10,000 workstations.</p>
          <p>However, our respondents report that devices in their organization are at various stages of enrollment and upgrade. For some organizations, nearly all of their devices are enrolled in an MDM, and nearly all their devices are upgraded to the latest operating system. Yet for others, not even a quarter of devices are enrolled and upgraded. This means that devices are being left exposed to compromise, and organizations are left in the dark on which ones.</p>
          <p>As for the basics of their MDMs, most (58%) are using a vendor-issued, cloud-based solution, while the rest are using a self-managed solution hosted by their organization. The types of devices most commonly covered by their MDMs include their network switches and other infrastructure at the top of the list, followed by laptops, virtual desktops, smartphones, and servers. Windows is the platform that respondents use the most in their office yet that isn’t covered by their MDM, and they also struggle the most to manage miscellaneous platforms, iOS, and Android.</p>
          <p>In our next section, we’ll look deeper at what makes their MDM approach successful and what challenges they face on a daily basis.</p>
