          <p>When it comes to their best practices and their top challenges, two points surface. The first is the necessity of having the right MDM solution in place that can monitor all devices, verify compliance, have accurate visibility into those endpoints, and that can do it all in real time. The second point that surfaces is that the first point can only be achieved if devices are enrolled in the first place. It’s part of the reason why the number one best practice was to have a documented policy in place for personal device usage. It’s also why the second biggest day-to-day challenge is getting all devices being used across their organization enrolled in their MDM.</p>
