          <h2>Summary</h2>
          <p>An organization with a growing number of endpoints across thousands of devices needs some way to manage them. For our respondents, the biggest trigger that got their organization to invest in an MDM solution was the move to remote work sparked by the pandemic and its sudden lockdowns. Other reasons for adopting an MDM include needing to ensure compliance for an audit, and wanting to have more of a hand involved in device management.</p>
          <p>But in addition to the challenges mentioned in the last section regarding enrollment, real-time monitoring, and visibility, our respondents also found challenges in actually deploying the MDM solution they need to secure their endpoints. While 18.7% said that their MDM took a month or less to deploy and implement, 22.2% said theirs took a year or longer to roll out — which is a long time to leave devices unmonitored and unaccounted for.</p>
          <p>They also encountered issues during deployment, as the MDM ended up being too complicated to understand, didn’t have helpful documentation, was too hard to configure, and didn’t integrate with SSO — and it was hard to get vendor support to help remedy the issues they faced.</p>
          <p>Once deployed and implemented, did our respondents find that they had an effective solution on their hands? As we’ll find out in the next section, many of them didn’t.</p>
